hospitals ambulatory surgery centers and radiation oncology centers  controversies  hospital licenses  allegations of noncompliance with samesex visitation law  fraudulent medicaid claims  buzzfeed investigation  references  external links company historyedit this section is in a list format that may be better presented using prose you can help by converting this section to prose if appropriate editing help is available april  alan b miller who currently serves as the company’s chairman and chief executive officer founded universal health services inc in  after he engineered a financial turnaround of american medicorp only to lose the control of the company in a hostile takeover by humana the next day miller founded uhs with  million from venture capitalists and  put up by himself and several former american medicorp employees who decided to follow miller into his new venture within  months of its founding uhs would own four hospitals and have management contracts with two additional hospitals  uhs entered las vegas with the purchase of valley hospital which has been part of uhs longer than any other hospital in the system the acquisition gave uhs its entry into the growing southeast nevada marketplace  the company’s annual gross revenue was  million  the company chose its first board of directors members included alan b miller sidney miller george h strong edwin c cohen leonard shaykin and thomas l kempner  uhs held its initial public offering analysts offered positive recommendations for the ipo because of significant and successful experience that company managers had with uhs and with american medicorp annual gross revenue at the time was  million  uhs purchased five hospitals from the stewards foundation marking the first time a forprofit corporation purchased hospitals from a nonprofit religious organization  uhs stock split for the first time  uhs purchased qualicare inc for more than  million the purchase included  acute care hospitals and four behavioral health hospitals giving the company its entry into the psychiatric healthcare market  universal health services inc was ranked first for growth in the healthcare industry over five years by financial world magazine  company revenues continued to increase as medicare introduced fixed payments for diagnostic related groups drgs a move experts said would benefit wellmanaged companies such as uhs  annual gross revenue exceeded  million for the first time  wellington regional medical center in wellington florida begins its operation  uhs created universal health realty income trust the first reit in the healthcare industry  uhs stock trading moved from nasdaq to nyse annual gross revenues exceeded  billion  inland valley medical center was chosen as one of the top  hospitals in the country by modern healthcare magazine  uhs stock split two for one outstanding shares increased from  million to  million annual gross revenue  billion  uhs acquires an  stake in george washington university hospital the company introduced its service excellence program to focus on making patients the first priority  uhs was named to the wall street journal’s “shareholder honor roll”  debra k osteen appointed vice president of uhs and president of the behavioral health division  uhs stock split two for one the wall street journal named uhs as the best performing healthcare stock over  years  uhs was listed among america’s best big companies in the forbes platinum   the replacement building for the george washington university hospital opened  steve filton was named chief operating officer  the wall street journal’s shareholder scorecard listed uhs as the best performing stock among healthcare providers from  to  charles boyle named controller cheryl ramagano appointed treasurer and jp christen promoted to assistant vice president of hospital finance  uhs makes the fortune  for the first time with a rank of   uhs was number  among the “top  places to work in it” by computerworld magazine  uhs formed uhs development company inc to build better quality hospitals at lower costs for the industry richard c wright was named president of the new venture  annual revenue reached  billion  uhs stock split two for one  uhs reached an agreement in may to acquire psychiatric solutions inc one of the nation’s largest behavioral health operators with  locations over  beds and a  percent market share for  billion as a result of the acquisition completed in november uhs more than doubled its beds count in the behavioral health segment and became the countrys top inpatient psychiatric services provider  uhs announced its plans to acquire ascend health corporation for  million adding  freestanding inpatient psychiatric facilities with  licensed beds in texas arizona utah oregon and washington state to its portfolio  the bed fivestory temecula valley hospital in temecula california begins its operation offering a comprehensive range of services similar to hospitals in large metropolitan areas with  affiliated physicians over  employees and  volunteers  a total of  facilities owned and operated by subsidiaries of uhs are recognized by the joint commission as a top performer on key quality measures® for  there are  behavioral health and five acute care hospitals listed including  facilities honored for the second consecutive year  uhs listed among fortune  with a rank of  and worlds most admired companies  a total of  facilities owned and operated by subsidiaries of universal health services inc are recognized by the joint commission as a top performer on key quality measures® for   uhs buys palo verde mental health with  beds for an undisclosed amount renaming the facility to palo verde behavioral health  uhs announced the acquisition of the psychiatric institute of washington a bed behavioral health care facility and outpatient treatment center located in the district of columbia as part of this transaction the company also acquired the arbor group llc which operates three management contracts covering  beds in the washington dc and maryland market  uhs acquires cygnet health care limited for approximately  million adding  facilities throughout the united kingdom including  inpatient behavioral health hospitals and  nursing homes with a total of  beds just a few days after the companys stock joined the sp index  uhs listed among fortune  worlds most admired companies and americas largest corporations  most meaningful companies to work for in america by business insider and a recipient of leadership  excellence awards   uhs expands its presence in the uk with the acquisition of alpha hospitals holdings limited a provider of low and medium secure mental health care facilities and services for  million from private equity group cc alpha group adding four hospitals and  beds to its portfolio  uhs announces the acquisition of foundations recovery network based in brentwood tennessee for  million adding  residential beds in four inpatient facilities and eight outpatient centers to its substance use disorder service line  a total of  facilities owned and operated by subsidiaries of uhs are recognized by the joint commission as a top performer on key quality measures® for   uhs buys desert view hospital in pahrump nevada with  beds for an undisclosed amount in  under miller’s leadership forbes recognized uhs as one of america’s top  public companies ranking  and uhs was named among fortune’s world’s most admired companies  on june   uhs under the leadership of miller ranked  on the fortune   facilitiesedit according to their annual report for fiscal year  uhs is running the following facilities acute care hospitalsedit aiken regional medical center aiken south carolina  beds owned aurora pavilion aiken south carolina  beds owned centennial hills hospital medical center las vegas nevada  beds owned corona regional medical center corona california  beds owned desert springs hospital las vegas nevada  beds owned doctors’ hospital of laredo laredo texas  beds owned doctors’ hospital er south laredo texas leased fort duncan regional medical center eagle pass texas  beds owned george washington university hospital washington dc  beds owned henderson hospital henderson nevada  beds owned lakewood ranch medical center bradenton florida  beds owned manatee memorial hospital bradenton florida  beds owned northern nevada medical center sparks nevada  beds owned northwest texas healthcare system amarillo texas  beds owned the pavilion at northwest texas healthcare system amarillo texas  beds owned palmdale regional medical center palmdale california  beds owned south texas health system edinburg regional medical center  children’s hospital edinburg texas  beds owned mcallen medical center mcallen texas  beds leased mcallen heart hospital mcallen texas  beds owned south texas behavioral health center mcallen texas  beds owned sths er at mission mission texas leased sths er at weslaco weslaco texas leased southwest healthcare system inland valley medical center wildomar california  beds leased rancho springs medical center murrieta california  beds owned spring valley hospital medical center las vegas nevada  beds owned st mary’s regional medical center enid oklahoma  beds owned summerlin hospital medical center las vegas nevada  beds owned temecula valley hospital temecula california  beds owned texoma medical center denison texas  beds owned tmc behavioral health center denison texas  beds owned valley hospital medical center las vegas nevada  beds owned wellington regional medical center west palm beach florida  beds leased outpatient behavioral health care facilitiesedit arbour counseling services rockland massachusetts owned arbour senior care rockland massachusetts owned behavioral educational services riverdale florida leased the canyon at santa monica santa monica california leased community cornerstones rio piedras puerto rico leased first home care portsmouth virginia leased foundations atlanta atlanta georgia leased foundations memphis memphis tennessee leased foundations nashville nashville tennessee leased foundations roswell roswell georgia leased foundations san diego san diego california leased foundations san francisco san francisco california leased good samaritan counseling center anchorage alaska owned michael’s house outpatient palm springs california leased st louis behavioral medicine institute st louis missouri owned talbott recovery atlanta georgia owned surgical hospitals ambulatory surgery centers and radiation oncology centersedit cancer care institute of carolina aiken south carolina owned cornerstone regional hospital edinburg texas leased palms westside clinic asc royal palm beach florida leased temecula valley day surgery and pain therapy center murrieta california leased controversiesedit hospital licensesedit the centers for medicare and medicaid services cms threatened the rancho springs medical center murrieta and inland valley regional medical center wildomar in california with decertification in june  while the state of california warned of a possible hospital license revocation universal health services implemented a program to address all concerns and in november  the two hospitals passed a cms certification survey as a result cms rescinded its termination notice and the california department of public health withdrew its license revocation notice allegations of noncompliance with samesex visitation lawedit according to a petition started on changeorg by terriann simonelli of henderson nevada spring valley hospital owned and operated by uhs claimed that their policy required power of attorney for a samesex partner to make medical decisions on behalf of their partner if true this would seemingly violate new department of health and human services rules enabling samesex partners to make said decisions with or without power of attorney fraudulent medicaid claimsedit in september  uhs and its subsidiaries keystone education and youth services llc and keystone marion llc dba keystone marion youth center agreed to pay over  million to resolve allegations that they submitted false and fraudulent claims to medicaid between october  and march  the entities allegedly provided substandard psychiatric counseling and treatment to adolescents in violation of the medicaid requirements the united states alleged that uhs falsely represented keystone marion youth center as a residential treatment facility providing inpatient psychiatric services to medicaid enrolled children when in fact it was a juvenile detention facility the united states further alleged that neither a medical director nor licensed psychiatrist provided the required direction for psychiatric services or for the development of initial or continuing treatment plans the settlement further resolved allegations that the entities filed false records or statements to medicaid when they filed treatment plans that falsely represented the level of services that would be provided to the patients buzzfeed investigationedit on december   buzzfeed published a report detailing questionable practices within uhs psychiatric facilities the report includes allegations of holding nonthreatening patients against their will manipulative misinterpretation of patient testimonies to fit guidelines to involuntary confinement aggressive staff layoffs and understaffing in hospitals needless patient deaths due to understaffing and misprescription of medication violating a patient’s right to be discharged or holding a patient without the proper documentation and unnecessary extension of stay times to the maximum medicare payout uhs denied the conclusions of the report its stock fell approximately  after publication referencesedit  health care groups that made this years fortune  list advisorycom the advisory board company  retrieved    form k  item  business edgar us securities and exchange commission  retrieved    kepos paula  international directory of company histories vol  st