nited states as of february   uhs operates through its subsidiaries  inpatient acute care hospitals  freestanding emergency departments and  inpatient and  outpatient behavioral health care facilities located in  states washington dc the united kingdom puerto rico and the us virgin islands the uhs facilities located in the us had approximately  employees as of december   of whom approximately  were employed fulltime in addition the facilities located in the uk had approximately  employees as of december   the company aims to provide quality healthcare at affordable cost strengthen physician and community relationships and pursue conservative growth contents  company history  facilities  acute care hospitals  outpatient behavioral health care facilities  surgical hospitals ambulatory surgery centers and radiation oncology centers  controversies  hospital licenses  allegations of noncompliance with samesex visitation law  fraudulent medicaid claims  buzzfeed investigation  references  external links company historyedit this section is in a list format that may be better presented using prose you can help by converting this section to prose if appropriate editing help is available april  alan b miller who currently serves as the company’s chairman and chief executive officer founded universal health services inc in  after he engineered a financial turnaround of american medicorp only to lose the control of the company in a hostile takeover by humana the next day miller founded uhs with  million from venture capitalists and  put up by himself and several former american medicorp employees who decided to follow miller into his new venture within  months of its founding uhs would own four hospitals and have management contracts with two additional hospitals  uhs entered las vegas with the purchase of valley hospital which has been part of uhs longer than any other hospital in the system the acquisition gave uhs its entry into the growing southeast nevada marketplace  the company’s annual gross revenue was  million  the company chose its first board of directors members included alan b miller sidney miller george h strong edwin c cohen leonard shaykin and thomas l kempner  uhs held its initial public offering analysts offered positive recommendations for the ipo because of significant and successful experience that company managers had with uhs and with american medicorp annual gross revenue at the time was  million  uhs purchased five hospitals from the stewards foundation marking the first time a forprofit corporation purchased hospitals from a nonprofit religious organization  uhs stock split for the first time  uhs purchased qualicare inc for more than  million the purchase included  acute care hospitals and four behavioral health hospitals giving the company its entry into the psychiatric healthcare market  universal health services inc was ranked first for growth in the healthcare industry over five years by financial world magazine  company revenues continued to increase as medicare introduced fixed payments for diagnostic related groups drgs a move experts said would benefit wellmanaged companies such as uhs  annual gross revenue exceeded  million for the first time  wellington regional medical center in wellington florida begins its operation  uhs created universal health realty income trust the first reit in the healthcare industry  uhs stock trading moved from nasdaq to nyse annual gross revenues exceeded  billion  inland valley medical center was chosen as one of the top  hospitals in the country by modern healthcare magazine  uhs stock split two for one outstanding shares increased from  million to  million annual gross revenue  billion  uhs acquires an  stake in george washington university hospital the company introduced its service excellence program to focus on making patients the first priority  uhs was named to the wall street journal’s “shareholder honor roll”  debra k osteen appointed vice president of uhs and president of the behavioral health division  uhs stock split two for one the wall street journal named uhs as the best performing healthcare stock over  years  uhs was listed among america’s best big companies in the forbes platinum   the replacement building for the george washington university hospital opened  steve filton was named chief operating officer  the wall street journal’s shareholder scorecard listed uhs as the best performing stock among healthcare providers from  to  charles boyle named controller cheryl ramagano appointed treasurer and jp christen promoted to assistant vice president of hospital finance  uhs makes the fortune  for the first time with a rank of   uhs was number  among the “top  places to work in it” by computerworld magazine  uhs formed uhs development company inc to build better quality hospitals at lower costs for the industry richard c wright was named president of the new venture  annual revenue reached  billion  uhs stock split two for one  uhs reached an agreement in may to acquire psychiatric solutions inc one of the nation’s largest behavioral health operators with  locations over  beds and a  percent market share for  billion as a result of the acquisition completed in november uhs more than doubled its beds count in the behavioral health segment and became the countrys top inpatient psychiatric services provider  uhs announced its plans to acquire ascend health corporation for  million adding  freestanding inpatient psychiatric facilities with  licensed beds in texas arizona utah oregon and washington state to its portfolio  the bed fivestory temecula valley hospital in temecula california begins its operation offering a comprehensive range of services similar to hospitals in large metropolitan areas with  affiliated physicians over  employees and  volunteers  a total of  facilities owned and operated by subsidiaries of uhs are recognized by the joint commission as a top performer on key quality measures® for  there are  behavioral health and five acute care hospitals listed including  facilities honored for the second consecutive year  uhs listed among fortune  with a rank of  and worlds most admired companies  a total of  facilities owned and operated by subsidiaries of universal health services inc are recognized by the joint commission as a top performer on key quality measures® for   uhs buys palo verde mental health with  beds for an undisclosed amount renaming the facility to palo verde behavioral health  uhs announced the acquisition of the psychiatric institute of washington a bed behavioral health care facility and outpatient treatment center located in the district of columbia as part of this transaction the company also acquired the arbor group llc which operates three management contracts covering  beds in the washington dc and maryland market  uhs acquires cygnet health care limited for approximately  million adding  facilities throughout the united kingdom including  inpatient behavioral health hospitals and  nursing homes with a total of  beds just a few days after the companys stock joined the sp index  uhs listed among fortune  worlds most admired companies and americas largest corporations  most meaningful companies to work for in america by business insider and a recipient of leadership  excellence awards   uhs expands its presence in the uk with the acquisition of alpha hospitals holdings limited a provider of low and medium secure mental health care facilities and services for  million from private equity group cc alpha group adding four hospitals and  beds to its portfolio  uhs announces the acquisition of foundations recovery network based in brentwood tennessee for  million adding  residential beds in four inpatient facilities and eight outpatient centers to its substance use disorder service line  a total of  facilities owned and operated by subsidiaries of uhs are recognized by the joint commission as a top performer on key quality measures® for   uhs buys dese